devdoc.author: Kamil Alizai Sadik

params._nftAddress: Address of NFT collection for which bid is being canceled

getBid(address,address).details: Getter function to display a single bid on front-end

params._nftAddress: Address of collection to which the bid applies

getBids(address[],address[]).details: Getter function to display multiple bids on front-end

params._nftAddresses: Array of collections to which each bid (respectively) applies

hitBid(address,address,uint256,uint256).details: Sells NFT into a bid (i.e., "hits" the bid)

params._expectedWeiPriceEach: Price (in wei) that seller expects to receive for each NFT
params._nftAddress: Address of collection to which the bid applies
params._tokenId: Token id of the NFT in question

hitMultipleBids(address[],address,uint25.details: Sells multiple NFTs into multiple bids (i.e., "hits" multiple bids)

params._expectedWeiPriceEach: Array of prices (in wei) that seller expects to receive for each NFT
params._nftAddress: Address of collection to which the bids apply
params._tokenIds: Array of token ids of the NFTs in question

returns._0: Array of proceeds remitted to seller for each sold NFT

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: A contract enabling bidders to bid on any NFT in a given collection, and holders to sell any NFT from that collection into such a bid
